Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.39,0:00:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were investigating to see if Mizunashi Rena and Hondou Eisuke's sister were the same person...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.27,0:00:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked to see if Mizunashi Rena's blood type was really AB.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have AB blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.24,0:00:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the answer to Eisuke's blood type...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was written in the child health record left behind in the mansion where his deceased mother had been a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.41,0:00:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, it's written right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.66,0:00:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hondou Eisuke, Type O."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.00,0:00:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves my blood type is O, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.72,0:00:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now all that remains is whether the story about sharing blood with his sister is true or not
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that same Okudaira mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.81,0:00:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The son, Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, had been killed by someone one year before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is a printout from a video that was recorded at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both legs bound, mouth gum taped —\hhow cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.57,0:00:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to know if anyone resented your son or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.99,0:01:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not aware of anyone on the outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.20,0:01:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what I believe, Detective Mouri:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son Tango's life was cut off by some very crafty person...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.80,0:01:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is living in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.87,0:01:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tingling suspense is building.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.67,0:01:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running in the darkness —\ha red scream and a black shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:01:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A screams resounds within the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:57.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:01:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:34.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,CLASH OF RED AND BLACK\NEXCLAMATION
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Your son was killed by someone inside the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.74,0:03:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it was while everyone in the house was watching a video in the living room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.45,0:03:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That somebody drowned your son in your pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.13,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Okudaira Kakuzou (63)\NHead of Okudaira Family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember, your son's estimated time of death was between 9:00 and 10:00 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For two hours before and after, in other words from 7:00 through 12:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you said everyone was watching some videos, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much is true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just can't help thinking that Tango's death was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The responsibility of someone in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.49,0:04:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a secret exit from the living room you can sneak out of or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's no secret door, but people did go to the restroom during the course of the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.75,0:04:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.71,0:04:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone snuck outside during a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restroom is connected to the living room, and its window isn't large enough for an adult to fit through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, wasn't it impossible for anyone in the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But look more closely...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.81,0:05:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, Tango's right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's wearing a white glove, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On this exact same day two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.66,0:05:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our previous butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fell off a cliff and died while he was driving the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.58,0:05:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the glove he always wore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the exact same day?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your son was killed on this day just a year ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it was today...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And three days after my son was killed, the butler's left-hand glove was found here in my study.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.36,0:05:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the criminal intended to put both gloves on your son but just happened to miss one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone must be holding a grudge over the previous butler's death...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A grudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:05:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't the butler's death just an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, someone believes you and your son caused that accident
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they put the butler's glove on your son and killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then left the other glove in this room to signal that you were next
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were gonna say that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.77,0:06:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't just come in on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said, "We're done with our other business, so let's go listen to the case."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.49,0:06:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No more "he-he-he."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.20,0:06:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're done, then hurry up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, Uncle Kakuzou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.64,0:06:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we came across some of your mother's effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:07:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and thanks to you, I've gotten them safely back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother was the most wonderful housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was so compassionate and was always smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for not being as compassionate or friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.37,0:07:17.37,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tabata Kikuyo (39)\NOkudaira Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, I didn't mean it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.91,0:07:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.46,0:07:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just asking Detective Mouri here to look into it further.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:34.43,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Segawa Hatarou (48)\NOkudaira Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.09,0:07:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please show Detective Mouri to the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you wish, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and also, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make some more coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.64,0:07:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, while you're at it, call my wife for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want her to help me organize the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.53,0:07:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as the two of you are available, come and help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have something to talk to you about as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:07:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.87,0:08:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.12,0:08:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Always knock before you come into my study!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.29,0:08:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to make that clear to the guests, you dimwit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.05,0:08:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.51,0:08:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wants me to help him organize the books in his study?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:26.36,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Okudaira Eiko (56)\NOkudaira's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.39,0:08:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man will find fault with every little detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earlier, when I tried to open the cardboard box with the set of large books that was delivered today, I really got scolded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "Don't touch that until I've opened it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's always changing the shelves in his bookcases around to fit those big books...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And eventually ends up having to move almost every book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.09,0:08:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he asks for my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.42,0:08:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.97,0:08:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll escort Detective Mouri to the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That will allow you go to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the other things, such as the repairs to Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one has used that car in the last two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.36,0:09:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can just leave it sit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.53,0:09:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.36,0:09:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the repairs to the car can wait, I'll leave the rest up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.45,0:09:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.04,0:09:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, this is the living room that was mentioned before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day all four of us, my husband and myself, the butler and the housekeeper were all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last year we were watching the videos of our overseas trip on and on for five hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't your son watch them with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.06,0:09:48.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it was because he was avoiding being around me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I'm not his real mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.98,0:09:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was my husband's son with his former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:09:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, are you sure my husband didn't say anything about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him suspecting us just because they haven't caught any culprits, my husband is becoming annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The attached restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An adult definitely couldn't get through this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no way to just secretly slip out of the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.60,0:10:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since all four of them were watching those videos here, they have perfect alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.27,0:10:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw that Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who was such a crybaby,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,brought such a cute girlfriend along with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.78,0:10:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-She isn't my girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We came because we wanted to know Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}'s blood type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.50,0:10:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said you'd found his child health records.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:11:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's this about your blood type?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I showed a picture of my sister to Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he said, "Isn't she that announcer, Mizunashi Rena?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.56,0:11:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we came here to clear up any uncertainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.19,0:11:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, that announcer has Type AB, while I have O.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since I received a transfusion from my sister, my sister and that announcer must be different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.08,0:11:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} already knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, I remember that happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.75,0:11:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was right after his mother died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.13,0:11:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was taken in by his father and moved to Osaka, that accident happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as I heard about it, I dashed right over there and found his sister sleeping beside his bed, completely exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:12:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked the nurse why, she said his sister had given him a large amount of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she told them, "You can draw out all of my blood for my little brother."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that what she said?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.95,0:12:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That settles it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister and Mizunashi Rena...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.13,0:12:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are not the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really watch that much TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.72,0:12:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they really that much alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.68,0:12:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister and that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.81,0:12:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the photo we saw, they were two halves of a melon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless they're doppelgangers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having two people who look so completely alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's connected to my sister's disappearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.66,0:12:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He became suspicious of Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.91,0:12:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then checked Uncle out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:12:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to obtain an invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.83,0:12:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he intended to ask her about his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He likely expects she would feign ignorance if he approached her directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why not meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, her...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.01,0:13:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might as well have them show us the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.93,0:13:15.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might discover something there about the son's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.69,0:13:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.48,0:13:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.19,0:13:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you go out somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.03,0:13:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we were out of milk for the coffee, so we out to buy some in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, forgive me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.50,0:13:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you show everyone to the pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take in the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, this place is dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:13:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been left this way since the incident a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the pool I always used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.11,0:14:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, this kid's clumsy no matter where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.75,0:14:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's the right size.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope my deceased son's clothes are of a size that fits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It fits well, so I guess he was also short?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is a little baggy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.06,0:14:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.68,0:14:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was known as a body builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your clothes are in the washer now, so wait for a bit, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.23,0:14:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I didn't see any coffee in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.49,0:14:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left it ready in the coffee maker before I went to go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see the coffee in the kitchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:15:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Master might have grown impatient and made it himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounded like it came from the Master's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.17,0:15:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.84,0:15:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hope it wasn't that expensive vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's always treasured that vase, considering it's worth ¥50,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.73,0:15:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.77,0:15:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.07,0:15:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:15:55.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go in, Mistress! On the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.01,0:15:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:15:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.31,0:16:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's hurry and get him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.44,0:16:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, call for an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.49,0:16:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:17.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, what's with this rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.87,0:16:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not coming undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.64,0:16:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the rim of the vase...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.22,0:16:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid it was too late by the time he made it to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.74,0:16:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.33,0:17:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's all right, I have two or three questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who first discovered the body was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first ones to discover my husband were Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard the sound of something breaking coming from the study, so we rushed here and knocked on the door, but he didn't respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he didn't answer when we called out, but when we started turning the door knob, he shouted, "Don't open it."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.74,0:17:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, did you open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.49,0:17:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.16,0:17:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we opened the door, we found the master's body hanging there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.21,0:17:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he did it just before you opened the door, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.51,0:17:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, his body was still swaying then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure we're talking suicide here, since the windows were securely locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he say, "Don't open it"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's obviously because he didn't want anyone to see him dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason he had grown tired of, the world and chose death instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at the fragments of the vase scattered on the floor, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must have been the source of the breaking sound we heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, this is a vase he cherished more than anything else and it's worth ¥50,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.30,0:18:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,¥50,000,000!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.88,0:18:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always talked about it, saying even ¥200,000,000 couldn't make up for that vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even used that vase as a footstool in order to kill himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.72,0:18:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Further proving he'd grown to hate this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The autopsy results say they found coffee and sleeping pills in the corpse's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:18:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:18:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.95,0:19:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are there two cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them was mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.24,0:19:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would he bother to take sleeping pills with the coffee before hanging himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he originally planned to take a lot of sleeping pills, but he got impatient and decided to change the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.80,0:19:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this time he applied glue to the knot of the rope to be sure it wouldn't come undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.84,0:19:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.80,0:19:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we were getting him down, we had a hard time getting the rope undone due to it being glued.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what reason did he have to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do any of you have any idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He requested we come to the study so he could tell us something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe he was distressed about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, why did he hang himself before discussing it with you all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.58,0:19:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have thought discussing it with us wouldn't help...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.71,0:20:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your husband didn't trust you very much, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.34,0:20:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood running from his mouth is likely from him biting his lip in regret
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't stand someone else inheriting his prize vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be why he broke it by using it as a footstool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.82,0:20:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he was really greedy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.07,0:20:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if he had used the vase as a footstool and it only made the noise when it fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have already hung himself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.04,0:20:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he weren't so greedy, he wouldn't have shouted "Don't take the vase" after that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't "Don't take" it was "Don't open."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.46,0:20:47.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: {\i1}Ageru na{\i0} means "Don't take", while {\i1}Akeru na{\i0} means "Don't open"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.34,0:20:45.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, that is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could someone hanging really be able to shout?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:20:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This means that when the vase broke, he hadn't hung himself yet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he was so shocked after breaking the vase that he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if you rushed here immediately after hearing it break, he didn't have time to prepare the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was because of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:14.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Killer from {\b1}Hades{\b0}\NShinmei Kaori
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, this book is stained with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have been upset if it were one of his important books.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.91,0:21:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Killer from Hades"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.54,0:21:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does seem to have been directly below his feet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:28.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.39,0:21:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were, the murderer must be a ghost from the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.86,0:21:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.57,0:21:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The word "Hades" is mostly covered in blood, and the droplets below resemble the "ko" character in hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Yomi-ko"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,(Calendar)\N"Ko-yomi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.24,0:21:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it something about a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.25,0:21:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure whether this is "ko" or not
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.67,0:22:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do this and turn it horizontally, it resembles the hiragana "i" as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.80,0:22:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if this really was a dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the master of the house, Kakuzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murdered by someone inside of this very house.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does the message left in blood mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.29,0:24:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cruel method.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.00,0:24:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The full extent of which we yet to grasp.
